oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Corinthian Missionary Baptist Church, 2000 December
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A photograph of Corinthian Missionary Baptist Church located at 819 Thirty-third Avenue North, in Nashville, Tennessee. The church was erected in 1934. The foundation is made of stone. The exterior walls are brick. The roof is gabled with shingles. The windows have metal bars covering the glass panes. The doors are metal. Special features include a cornerstone. Forms part of the Historic Nashville, Inc. Sacred Sites Survey Project. 1 photograph : col. ; 4 x 6 in.
